ew/changed (visible as '2 changed' in the test-provider row and reviewable via Accept in the Panel). User then opens a third, unrelated story and clicks 'Run visual tests' for just that story (PanelView's `runCurrent` -&gt; `{type:'run', scope:'current', storyId}`). `VisualTestRunner.run()` synchronously calls `this.completed.clear()` and then sets `this.state = run.state` where `run.state.results` contains only the one just-selected story. The two previously-flagged stories vanish from `state.results`, so TestProviderRow now shows '0 changed'/'No visual changes detected' even though those two diffs were never reviewed or approved, and if the user later returns to one of those stories and clicks Accept, `approve()` finds no matching entry in `completed` and throws 'Stale visual approval; rerun the visual test before approving' — silently losing reviewable work with no warning that it happened.\",\"category\":\"correctness\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\"},{\"file\":\"packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/node/runner.ts\",\"line\":400,\"summary\":\"isMissing() duplicates isMissingPathError() in paths.ts verbatim instead of importing it\",\"failure_scenario\":\"The identical ENOENT/ENOTDIR-check function body exists in two files (runner.ts:400-406 and paths.ts:139-145); a future change to what counts as a 'missing file' error (e.g. adding EISDIR handling) has to be made in both places, and it's easy to update one and forget the other, silently reintroducing the bug the fix was meant to close in only one of the two call sites.\",\"category\":\"cleanup\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\"},{\"file\":\"packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/node/runner.ts\",\"line\":307,\"summary\":\"finishCapture reads baseline.png and baseline.json sequentially instead of in parallel\",\"failure_scenario\":\"readFileIfPresent(paths.baselinePath) and readJsonIfPresent(paths.baselineMetadataPath) are two independent, unrelated file reads awaited one after another for every story in every run; r